name: Chip Channel Restorations
description:
My name is Chip and welcome to my YouTube channel. I enjoy restoring old worn out items and recording it to share with all of you! I'm currently working on old pressed steel toys like, Tonka, Buddy L, Nylint, Structo, Keystone, Marx, Wyandotte, etc. However, As I get moved into a larger shop building, I'd like to start restoring some old Ride on Toys, Pedal Cars, and some larger projects possibly some motorcycles. Thank you for all your support!

Are any items for sale?
- Currently these are only for my personal collection

Where do I get these items?
- eBay, local antique stores, garage sales, Facebook market place, donations from viewers

Do I restore for Hire?
Unfortunely No, I only restore for my own personal collection and video creation

Where am I from?
- I live in Grand Island, NE central United States

Thank you for watching!

name: Michael Restoration
description: Welcome to Michael Restoration! We specialize in restoring vintage motorcycles, bringing them back to life and preserving their timeless allure. Join us on an exhilarating journey of transformation as we revive each bike, meticulously repairing and refurbishing every component. Experience the magic of restoration as worn surfaces are transformed into polished beauty, and listen to the triumphant roar of engines awakening once again. Whether you're a motorcycle enthusiast, a restorer, or simply appreciate the elegance of vintage bikes, our channel offers an immersive experience. Subscribe now to Michael Restoration and embark on a captivating adventure celebrating the art of motorcycle restoration. Discover the craftsmanship, uncover the rich history, and be inspired by the beauty of these iconic machines. Let us ignite your passion for vintage motorcycles and the artistry of bringing them back to life.

name: Veradona Restoration
description:
Veradona Restoration

My name is Radek Pavelka.

About 20 years ago I got my first antique coal iron from my wife.
I liked it so much, that I started to collect them and repared the damaged.
Restoration is my hobby and I try to improve myself constantly and learn new and new things. I renovate both wooden and iron things and try to keep as many original parts as possible.
People found my work interesting and they started to send me various things for renovation.

I would like to share with you these videos, if you like it, please, subscribe my channel, give me a like or share it.

Thanks for all your support, I really do appreciate it :-)

Have a nice day!

No one is allowed to use any of my content. So don't send me please Emails about this - Thank you .
